  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Infection in the intervertebral disc space\noccurs post surgically in approximately 1-2% of patients after spinal surgery.\nInfection of nucleus pulposus due to infection of vertebral body end-plate cartilage\nRisk Factors: pediatric patients (age < 8yo), post-op, immunocompromised",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": ">90% present with unremitting neck or\nback pain\nwhich awakens them at night\nMay have radicular symptoms\nFever (60-70%)\nNeuro deficits (10-50%)\nESR elevation (>90%)\nLeukocytosis (<50%)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "back pain",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Back_pain"
        }
      ]
    },
